A typical example is to use it as the request or the response type of an API method. For instance: service Foo { rpc Bar(google.protobuf.Empty) returns (google.protobuf.Empty); }

uncommittedFileChanges.description: A list of all files which have uncommitted Git changes. There will only be a single entry for any given file.

relationDescriptor.description: Descriptor for the relation and its columns. Used as documentation only, i.e. values here will result in no changes to the relation's metadata.

Declaration.description: Represents a relation which is not managed by Dataform but which may be referenced by Dataform actions.

remoteBranch.description: Optional. The name of the branch in the Git remote from which to pull commits. If left unset, the repository's default branch name will be used.

author.description: Required. The author of any merge commit which may be created as a result of merging fetched Git commits into this workspace.

sqlScript.description: Output only. The generated BigQuery SQL script that will be executed.

BigQueryAction.description: Represents a workflow action that will run against BigQuery.

emailAddress.description: Required. The commit author's email address.

CommitAuthor.description: Represents the author of a Git commit.

directory.description: A child directory in the directory.

DirectoryEntry.description: Represents a single entry in a workspace directory.

bigqueryPolicyTags.description: A list of BigQuery policy tags that will be applied to the column.

path.description: The identifier for the column. Each entry in `path` represents one level of nesting.

description.description: A textual description of the column.

newPath.description: Required. The new path for the directory including directory name, rooted at workspace root.

path.description: Required. The directory's full path including directory name, relative to the workspace root.
